cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SC, cs.SE, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses the performance and scalability bottlenecks in large scientific applications, which are often addressed through parallel computing and distributed systems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper focuses on the I/O systems and storage technologies used in scientific applications, which are often related to data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.SC (Scientific Computing and Numerical Analysis): The paper specifically addresses the performance and scalability issues in scientific applications, which are a key focus of this sub-category. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the usage of object storage in scientific applications, which may require software engineering techniques to integrate and optimize. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the usage of object storage as a potential solution to scalability and performance issues in scientific applications, which may involve systems and control theory.
